'''Masashi Ikari''' (井狩 正司, 1916–2011) was a Japanese scholar of national literature. In 1934, he graduated from the former {{ill|Nihon University First Junior High School and High School|ja|日本大学第一中学校・高等学校}} (now Nihon University First High School). He served as a professor at the {{ill|Faculty of Letters and Sciences, Nihon University|ja|日本大学文理学部}} and as the chief priest of {{ill|Sumida River Shrine|ja|隅田川神社}}.
== Major Works == * ''Heike Monogatari: Ruijū Shōhon'' (平家物語：類従抄本). Tokyo Shoin, 1948. * ''Kenreimon'in Ukyo no Daibu-shū'' (建礼門院右京大夫集). Tōhō Shobō, May 1956. * ''Kōhon Kenreimon'in Ukyo no Daibu-shū'' (校本建礼門院右京大夫集). Tōhō Shobō, May 1959. * ''Kōhon Kenreimon'in Ukyo no Daibu-shū'' (校本建礼門院右京大夫集). Kasama Shoin, April 1967. * ''Sarashina Nikki'' (更級日記). {{ill|Ōfūsha|ja|桜楓社}} (later Ōfū), April 25, 1968. * ''Kenreimon'in Ukyo no Daibu-shū: Kōhon oyobi Sōsakuin'' (建礼門院右京大夫集：校本及び総索引). Kasama Shoin, 1969 (Edited). * ''Gomotsuhon Sarashina Nikki'' (御物本更級日記). Ōfūsha (later Ōfū), 1970.
== See Also == * {{ill|Faculty of Letters and Sciences, Nihon University|ja|日本大学文理学部}} * {{ill|Chitarō Suzuki|ja|鈴木知太郎}} * {{ill|Tadanori Yanagida|ja|柳田忠則}}
